1. Assume two sensors that monitor the health of a press machine in a factory assembly line send their data to a Kafka topic PressData
for predictive maintenance analysis. The order of data of each sensor and across the two sensors is important to draw valid conclusions. 
Two applications A1 and A2 perform independent analytics processing of the sensor data. 
How many partitions should topic PressData have and how many consumer groups should be created for this scenario?
----------------------------
The Kafka topic should have one partition because message ordering must be preserved both within each sensor and across the two sensors. 
Kafka guarantees ordering only within a single partition, so using more partitions would break the global order. 
Additionally, there should be two consumer groups, one for each application (A1 and A2), so that both applications can independently 
consume all the data from the topic.
