2. Consider a distributed banking application that is required to be available 24/7/365. What property must be sacrificed under this assumption and why?
----------------------------
In a distributed banking system that must be available at all times (24/7/365), consistency must be sacrificed. 
According to the CAP theorem, in the presence of network partitions, a system can guarantee either consistency or availability, but not both. 
Since availability is required, the system may return slightly outdated or inconsistent data during failures.
