3. Explain what is Eventual Consistency. Give an example of an application for which eventual consistency is acceptable.
----------------------------
Eventual consistency is a model where updates to a system are not immediately visible to all nodes, but all replicas will eventually become consistent 
if no new updates occur. This means temporary inconsistencies are allowed. 
A typical example is Instagram, where a newly uploaded post may not appear instantly to all users but will become visible to everyone after a short time.
